      "score": 2,
      "text": "Seriously, I looked everywhere I couldn&#x27;t find anything that does the following in a straight forward way and with minimalist UI:<p>- Shortcut to show region selection (Something like taking a screenshot in Windows (SHIFT+WIN+S)<p>- After region selection, start recording immediately<p>- Stop recording and save in a predefined location<p>Features:<p>- Configure in advance whether to save as MP3 or GIF<p>Every tool I tried is either too bloated or has some extra steps that ruins the fluidity of UX.<p>The closest thing I found is LiceCap, but this tool is GIF exclusive and has extra UI steps.<p>For someone that takes screen recordings every day, any tool becomes too tedious.<p>I wish I could build it my self, but time constraints.",
